Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.05,0:00:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Day 13.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.40,0:00:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I lost 40 dollars to a position that didn't exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.35,0:00:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}My own bot had lied to me for five and a half hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.88,0:00:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I can't code.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.26,0:00:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}9 years in crypto.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.38,0:00:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}AI trades my thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.57,0:00:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Day 13.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.94,0:00:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}The bot hit a stop loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.01,0:00:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Fired a market sell to close the long.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.88,0:00:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}From its point of view — closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.08,0:00:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Problem was — the order it sent to Coinbase had no close flag.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.14,0:00:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}The exchange treated it as a brand new short.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.39,0:00:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Result?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.34,0:00:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Long got netted.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.93,0:00:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Short got opened.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.54,0:00:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Five and a half hours later I opened the app manually and found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.22,0:00:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}What scared me wasn't the 40 dollars.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.01,0:00:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}It was — every monitor I had said everything was fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.08,0:00:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}The bot's logs said okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.25,0:00:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Risk said okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.72,0:00:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}You could only see the ghost from outside the system.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.99,0:00:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}The most dangerous kind of failure is the one that doesn't announce itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.71,0:01:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}It doesn't crash, doesn't error, doesn't warn.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.28,0:01:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}It just quietly makes your numbers slightly wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.86,0:01:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Day 14 tomorrow — I fixed it with 3 lines of code.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.53,0:01:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Follow along.
